<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:40PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Garfield and eastern Iron Counties through 330 PM MDT...
At 239 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Panguitch, or 31 miles south of Beaver. This storm was nearly
stationary.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Panguitch.
This includes US Route 89 between mile markers 128 and 142.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
